==English==
[[Image:Haeckel Florideae Chondrus crispus.png|thumb|'''Irish moss''' (''[[Chondrus crispus]]'')]]

===Etymology===
{{sense|seaweed}} From its frequency on the Irish coast.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
{{wikipedia}}

# A species of edible [[seaweed]], ''[[Chondrus crispus]]''.
#* '''1865''', {{w|Henry David Thoreau}}, ''Cape Cod'', Chapter I. "The Shipwreck", page 13.
#*: At Jerusalem village the inhabitants were collecting in haste, before a thunder-shower now approaching, the '''Irish moss''' which they had spread to dry.
# {{taxlink|Mastocarpus stellatus|species|ver=200629}} ({{vern|false Irish moss}}), a less commonly gathered seaweed.
# {{taxlink|Gracilaria|genus|ver=200629}}, a genus of seaweeds, cultivated and eaten in Asian cuisines.
# {{taxlink|Soleirolia soleirolii|species|ver=200629}} ([[angel's tears]]), a [[plant]] in the [[nettle]] family.
# {{taxlink|Sagina subulata|species|ver=200629}} (syns. {{taxlink|Sagina alexandrae|species|ver=200629}}), {{vern|heath pearlwort}}, a terrestrial plant with needle-like leaves.
# {{taxlink|Arenaria verna|species|ver=200629}} ({{vern|golden moss}})

